DHARAMSALA - Australia were bowled out for 137 in their second innings Monday, setting India a target of 106 runs to win the series-deciding fourth Test in Dharamsala.The tourists collapsed during the final session on the third day of the match after Umesh Yadav, Ravindra Jadeja and Ravichandran Ashwin picked up three wickets each.READ: Jadeja half-century puts India ahead of AustraliaOther than Glenn Maxwell, who top-scored with 45, no other Aussie batsman showed application on what appeared to be a sporting track.With the series tied 1-1, a victory in Dharamsala would see India snatch the Border-Gavaskar trophy from Australia, who triumphed at home in 2014-2015. AFP